===Verb===
{{en-verb|vilif|ies}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To say [[defamatory]] things about someone or something; to [[speak ill of]].
#: ''Out of jealousy, he tried to '''vilify''' his co-worker with lies and compared his co-worker to a sinister and bitesome cobra and a psychopath.''
#: {{syn|en|abuse|assail|criticize|decry|denigrate|demonize|denounce|libel|revile|slander|run down|Thesaurus:defame}}
#: {{ant|en|glorify|praise}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[belittle]] through speech; to [[put down]].
#: {{syn|en|berate|Thesaurus:criticize}}
#: {{ant|en|glorify|praise}}

